title: Microsoft Windows 10 Enterprise x32 14393.10 en-US Activated
description:
murphy78 presents Windows 10 Enterprise 14393.10 Activated

No Windows 10 Settings were harmed in the making of this ISO.
No Programs are added to Windows.
No Unattended Settings were added to the installation.
No Registry Settings were modified.

32-bit Source:
en_windows_10_enterprise_version_1607_updated_jul_2016_x86_dvd_9060097.iso

Installation Index:
Windows 10 Enterprise

Release File: Win10Ent_14393.10_x32_en-US-PA.iso
Size: 2.30 GB
SHA-1: E03058D330F6F1E517F64DD60D802A3885466B20

Language: en-US (English - United States)

Tools used:
dism for Windows Updates integration
oscdimg for ISO mastering
Microsoft DaRT 10
murphy78 diskpart script v1.2.8

DISM /add-package and /resetbase (Indexes, Boot, Winre):
KB3176929

Features:
-MS DaRT 10 added to recovery options on both boot and winre
-Some useful scripts added to iso.
-DiskPart setup script v1.2.8 - Just boot to setup media
and press shift-f10 to bring up console and then type "Menu"
-UEFI support for 32-bit processors

Instructions:
-Use a USB program such as RUFUS to put this on a USB
Flash drive for boot installs.
-Alternatively, if you still use physical media, you can
burn the iso to a dvdr or greater.

NOTICE:
This version is pre-activated and will self-reactivate.
It uses abbodi's v10 KMS_VL_ALL OEM folder which I've left in
the sources folder on the ISO. If you ever want to remove the
pre-activated/re-activating portion of this setup, you just
delete the $oem$ folder inside sources within the iso.

I've left my usual scripts folder in the iso, but being as this
is a fairly new Win10 build, I don't know if all of them function
as intended. The KMS Gen ticket block reg key is already set by
the KMS_VL_ALL script. I'll include a link to abbodi's project
in case you wish to try to understand more.

Credits:
abbodi1406, qewlpal - KMS Activator
murphy78 - Integration, ISO design, Script and testing

Enjoy,
murphy78 :)
